Write a Python program to read the monthly salary of a person and his expenses under four categories: bank loan, hostel fees, food expenses, and parents’ support.
ANSWER:
salary=int(input())
bank=int(input())
hostel=int(input())
food=int(input())
parents=int(input())
spend=bank+hostel+food+parents
if(spend<salary):
 print("he can save the money")
elif(spend==salary):
 print("he can manage the money")
else:
 print("he want's to work hard")
